## Introduction

Game "Untangle" is one of Simon Tatham's puzzle collection, which can be found [here](https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/puzzles/js/untangle.html).
The goal of this game is to untangle all of the lines.

![Untangled](https://res.cloudinary.com/dzguym5xd/image/upload/v1672046556/coding2_wcasoo.png)

So that it looks like the picture below.

![Tangled](https://res.cloudinary.com/dzguym5xd/image/upload/v1672046351/coding1_qnsgpj.png)

Lines shouldn't be touching each other.

## How to Play

- You may move the dots with your mouse.
- If you finish untangling, then the screen will blink and tell you that the game is over.
- You can change the number of dots shown in the picture below.
![difficulty](https://res.cloudinary.com/dzguym5xd/image/upload/v1672049305/coding3_jiufae.png)

Hope you enjoy the puzzle!
